%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.business-standard.com%2Feconomy%2Fnews%2Fofficial-employment-data-masks-india-s-jobs-problem-say-economists-124071000385_1.html%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww-business--standard-com.cdn.ampproject.org%2Fc%2Fs%2Fwww.business-standard.com%2Famp%2Feconomy%2Fnews%2Fofficial-employment-data-masks-india-s-jobs-problem-say-economists-124071000385_1.html%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.business-standard.com%2Famp%2Feconomy%2Fnews%2Fofficial-employment-data-masks-india-s-jobs-problem-say-economists-124071000385_1.html%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22'Not%20Charity%2C%20Right'%3A%20Supreme%20Court's%20Big%20Alimony%20Order%20For%20Muslim%20Women%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cp%3EA%20divorced%20Muslim%20woman%20can%20seek%20alimony%20from%20her%20husband%20under%20Section%20125%20of%20the%20Code%20of%20Criminal%20Procedure%20-%20the%20law%20related%20to%20maintenance%20for%20wives%20-%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20ruled%20today.%20The%20big%20judgment%20came%20as%20a%20bench%20of%20Justice%20BV%20Nagarathna%20and%20Justice%20Augustine%20George%20Masih%20dismissed%20a%20Muslim%20man's%20petition%20challenging%20a%20direction%20to%20pay%20his%20wife%20maintenance%20after%20divorce.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20are%20hereby%20dismissing%20the%20criminal%20appeal%20with%20the%20major%20conclusion%20that%20Section%20125%20would%20be%20applicable%20to%20all%20women%20and%20not%20just%20married%20women%2C%26quot%3B%20Justice%20Nagarathna%20said.%20Justice%20Nagarathna%20and%20Justice%20Masih%20delivered%20separate%2C%20but%20concurrent%2C%20judgments.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20bench%20made%20it%20clear%20that%20the%20law%20for%20seeking%20maintenance%20applies%20to%20all%20married%20women%2C%20irrespective%20of%20their%20religion.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESection%20125%20broadly%20says%20a%20person%20with%20sufficient%20means%20cannot%20deny%20maintenance%20to%20their%20wife%2C%20children%20or%20parents.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMaintenance%2C%20the%20court%20said%2C%20is%20not%20charity%2C%20but%20the%20right%20of%20married%20women.%20In%20strong%20remarks%2C%20Justice%20Nagarathna%20said%2C%20%26quot%3BSome%20husbands%20are%20not%20conscious%20of%20the%20fact%20that%20the%20wife%2C%20who%20is%20a%20homemaker%2C%20is%20dependent%20on%20them%20emotionally%20and%20in%20other%20ways.%20The%20time%20has%20come%20when%20the%20Indian%20man%20must%20recognise%20a%20homemaker's%20role%20and%20sacrifice.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EThe%20Case%2C%20The%20Arguments%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20landmark%20judgment%20has%20come%20on%20a%20petition%20by%20Mohd%20Abdul%20Samad%2C%20who%20was%20directed%20by%20a%20family%20court%20to%20pay%20a%20monthly%20allowance%20to%20his%20divorced%20wife.%20Mr%20Samad%20challenged%20the%20direction%2C%20but%20the%20Telangana%20High%20Court%20refused%20to%20intervene.%20He%20then%20moved%20the%20Supreme%20Court.%20His%20counsel%20argued%20that%20divorced%20Muslim%20women%20can%20seek%20recourse%20to%20the%20Muslim%20Women%20(Protection%20of%20Rights%20on%20Divorce)%20Act%2C%201986%20Act%20and%20stressed%20that%20it%20provides%20much%20more%20than%20what%20Section%20125%20CrPC%20does.%20He%20also%20argued%20that%20a%20special%20law%20--%20referring%20to%20the%20Act%20--%20shall%20prevail%20over%20a%20general%20law.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAmicus%20Curiae%20Gaurav%20Agarwal%20countered%20that%20the%20personal%20law%20does%20not%20take%20away%20a%20woman's%20entitlement%20to%20relief%20under%20the%20gender-neutral%20CrPC.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EThe%20History%2C%20The%20Significance%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ETo%20understand%20the%20significance%20of%20this%20judgment%2C%20there%20is%20a%20need%20to%20go%20back%20to%20the%20Shah%20Bano%20case%20in%201985.%20In%20this%20landmark%20verdict%2C%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20had%20ruled%20that%20Section%20125%20of%20CrPC%20applies%20to%20everyone%2C%20irrespective%20of%20their%20religion.%20This%20was%2C%20however%2C%20diluted%20by%20the%20Muslim%20Women%20(Protection%20of%20Rights%20on%20Divorce)%20Act%2C%201986%2C%20that%20stated%20that%20the%20Muslim%20woman%20can%20seek%20maintenance%20only%20during%20iddat%20--%2090%20days%20after%20the%20divorce.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%202001%2C%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20upheld%20the%20Constitutional%20validity%20of%20the%201986%20Act%2C%20but%20ruled%20that%20the%20obligation%20of%20a%20man%20to%20provide%20maintenance%20to%20his%20divorced%20wife%20extends%20till%20she%20remarries%20or%20is%20able%20to%20support%20herself.%20Today's%20order%20further%20consolidates%20a%20divorced%20woman's%20order%20to%20seek%20alimony%20under%20CrPC%2C%20irrespective%20of%20her%20religion.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1720596000000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.ndtvimg.com%2Fi%2F2018-02%2Fmuslim-women_650x400_41518833970.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Findia-news%2Fmuslim-women-entitled-to-alimony-on-divorce-rules-supreme-court-6073157%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22A%20divorced%20Muslim%20woman%20can%20seek%20alimony%20from%20her%20husband%20under%20Section%20125%20of%20the%20Code%20of%20Criminal%20Procedure%2C%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20ruled%20today.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A1%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Findia-news%2Fmuslim-women-entitled-to-alimony-on-divorce-rules-supreme-court-6073157%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww-ndtv-com.cdn.ampproject.org%2Fc%2Fs%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Findia-news%2Fmuslim-women-entitled-to-alimony-on-divorce-rules-supreme-court-6073157%2Famp%2F1%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Findia-news%2Fmuslim-women-entitled-to-alimony-on-divorce-rules-supreme-court-6073157%2Famp%2F1%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22'Beginning%20of%20two%20legends'%3A%20Photos%20of%20Messi%20and%20baby%20Lamine%20Yamal%20resurface%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1720595876000%