nt%20the%20medics%20flying%20across%20the%20room.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EShards%20of%20glass%20tore%20into%20Holubchenko's%20back%20and%20his%20colleague%20Ihor%20Kolodka's%20face.%20The%20baby%20remained%20in%20place%20on%20the%20table%2C%20surrounded%20by%20shattered%20equipment%20and%20five%20bleeding%20adults.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIs%20everyone%20alive%3F%26quot%3B%20Holubchenko%20recalls%20shouting.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAnaesthesiologist%20Yaroslav%20Ivanov%20grabbed%20the%20manual%20resuscitator%20to%20keep%20the%20baby%20breathing%20after%20the%20ventilator%20broke.%20Worried%20the%20ceiling%20would%20collapse%2C%20some%20members%20of%20the%20team%20ran%20to%20the%20basement%20with%20Taras.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThese%20were%20the%20dramatic%20moments%20after%20a%20missile%20struck%20Okhmatdyt%20Children's%20Hospital%20in%20central%20Kyiv%20on%20Monday%2C%20an%20assault%20that%20shocked%20Ukrainians%20and%20prompted%20angry%20condemnation%20from%20Kyiv%20and%20its%20Western%20allies.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20U.N.%20said%20on%20Tuesday%20there%20was%20a%20%26quot%3Bhigh%20likelihood%26quot%3B%20the%20hospital%20took%20a%20direct%20hit%20from%20a%20Russian%20missile%20during%20a%20series%20of%20airstrikes%20on%20Ukrainian%20cities%20that%20have%20killed%20at%20least%2044%20people.%20The%20Kremlin%20has%20said%2C%20without%20providing%20evidence%2C%20that%20it%20was%20Ukrainian%20anti-missile%20fire%2C%20not%20Russia%2C%20that%20hit%20the%20hospital%2C%20large%20parts%20of%20which%20were%20reduced%20to%20rubble.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ETwo%20adults%20were%20killed%20at%20Okhmatdyt%20and%20dozens%20were%20wounded.%20Many%20patients%2C%20relatives%20and%20staff%20had%20fled%20to%20basements%20in%20time%20to%20avoid%20the%20worst%20of%20the%20blast.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BFor%20me%2C%20Okhmatdyt%20was%20the%20safest%20place%20for%20kids%20and%20adults.%20On%20that%20day%2C%20I%20realized%20there%20are%20no%20safe%20spaces%20left%20anywhere%2C%26quot%3B%20Ivanov%2C%2039%2C%20told%20Reuters%20over%20the%20telephone%20on%20Tuesday%20as%20he%20recovered%20from%20concussion%20and%20cuts.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhen%20they%20reached%20the%20basement%2C%20Ivanov%20and%20his%20colleagues%20found%20a%20room%20free%20of%20smoke%20and%20away%20from%20the%20screams%20of%20the%20injured.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThere%20they%20brought%20the%20baby%20back%20to%20consciousness%20and%20handed%20him%20over%20to%20a%20team%20of%20doctors%20to%20continue%20the%20surgery%20at%20another%20hospital.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch3%3E%3Cstrong%3ESTRAIGHT%20BACK%20TO%20WORK%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh3%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAs%20Holubchenko%20and%20Ivanov%20took%20care%20of%20Taras%2C%20Kolodka%20took%20out%20shards%20of%20glass%20from%20his%20face%20and%20then%20rushed%20outside%20to%20see%20how%20he%20could%20help.%20He%20saw%20that%20the%20toxicology%20department%20had%20been%20flattened.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BSince%20I%20was%20not%20bleeding%20anymore%2C%20I%20went%20outside%20to%20keep%20helping%20the%20injured%20and%20deal%20with%20the%20aftermath%20of%20the%20missile%20strike%2C%26quot%3B%20Kolodka%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIn%20the%20moment%2C%20we%20didn't%20think%20about%20whether%20it%20was%20easy%20or%20difficult%20-%20we%20were%20just%20doing%20our%20job%20and%20trying%20to%20help.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAfter%20helping%20rescue%20workers%20and%20soldiers%20sift%20through%20the%20rubble%20for%20the%20rest%20of%20the%20day%20in%20the%20dust%20and%20heat%2C%20he%20returned%20home%20to%20find%20there%20was%20no%20power.%20Electricity%20outages%20are%20now%20common%20across%20the%20country%20as%20Russia%20targets%20the%20energy%20system.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EKolodka%20woke%20up%20at%205%20a.m.%20to%20take%20a%20shower%20before%20heading%20back%20to%20work.%20Holubchenko%20also%20returned%20to%20the%20hospital%20on%20Tuesday.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20had%20to%20go%20because%20there%20was%20a%20meeting%20with%20colleagues%2C%20to%20see%