ed%22%3A1720556124000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F668d5a7a268f62ba18a87060%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhow-ukraine-could-get-air-superiority-use-f-16s-experts-2024-7%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22With%20F-16%20fighter%20jets%20about%20to%20enter%20the%20battle%2C%20a%20big%20question%20is%20how%20best%20to%20use%20them.%20Two%20airpower%20experts%20have%20a%20plan%20in%20mind.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22cpanella%40businessinsider.com%20(Chris%20Panella)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A586%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhow-ukraine-could-get-air-superiority-use-f-16s-experts-2024-7%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22How%20to%20read%20the%20UV%20index%20scale%20and%20why%20it's%20crucial%20for%20preventing%20skin%20cancer%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221199%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20model%20and%20a%20child%20model%20apply%20sunscreen%20in%20the%20sun%20on%20a%20bright%20blue%20day.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F668d929cb2528216eeb4e8cd%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22599%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EIf%20the%20UV%20index%20is%20high%2C%20it's%20crucial%20you%20wear%20sunscreen%2C%20seek%20shade%2C%20and%20cover%20up%20in%20protective%20clothing.%3Cp%3ESupergoop%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3ERadiation%20from%20the%20sun's%20ultraviolet%20(UV)%20rays%20can%20cause%20lasting%20damage%20to%20your%20skin.%20In%20fact%2C%20UV%20rays%20are%20the%20leading%20cause%20of%20skin%20cancers%2C%20like%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.aimatmelanoma.org%2Fmelanoma-101%2Fprevention%2Fwhat-is-ultraviolet-uv-radiation%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Emelanoma%20and%20basal%20cell%20carcinoma%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20says%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fmodernritual.com%2Fpages%2Fabout-mr%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EBeth%20Goldstein%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20MD%2C%20a%20dermatologist%20with%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.centraldermcenter.com%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ECentral%20Dermatology%20Center%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETherefore%2C%20it's%20important%20to%20monitor%20the%20UV%20index%20in%20your%20area%20before%20spending%20time%20outside.%20This%20can%20help%20protect%20you%20from%20sun%20damage%20and%20subsequent%20health%20consequences%20down%20the%20line.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EWhat%20is%20the%20UV%20index%3F%C2%A0%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.epa.gov%2Fenviro%2Fuv-index-description%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eultraviolet%20index%3C%2Fa%3E%20or%20UV%20index%20forecasts%20the%20intensity%20of%20the%20sun's%20UV%20rays%20on%20a%20scale%20of%200%20to%2011%2B.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EUnderstanding%20the%20index%20helps%20you%20predict%20how%20quickly%20your%20skin%20will%20burn%20if%20exposed%20to%20the%20sun%20and%20what%20kind%20of%20preventative%20actions%20you%20should%20take%20if%20planning%20to%20be%20outside.%20For%20example%2C%20the%20higher%20the%20UV%20index%20number%2C%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.curemelanoma.org%2Fabout-melanoma%2Fprevention%2Fuv-index%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ethe%20stronger%20the%20UV%20rays%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20and%20the%20faster%20you%20are%20likely%20to%20burn.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20US%20National%20Weather%20Service%20(NWS)%20and%20the%20EPA%20measure%20UV%20levels%20daily%20using%20a%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.epa.gov%2Fsunsafety%2Fcalculating-uv-index-0%23%3A~%3Atext%3DA%2520computer%2520model%2520uses%2520the%2Cof%2520day%2520(solar%2520noon).%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ecomputer%20model%20that%20analyzes%3C%2Fa%3E%20ground-level%20strength%20of%20UV%20radiation%20along%20with%20forecasted%20cloud%20cover%20and%20ozone%20concentration.%20You%20can%20see%20the%20UV%20index%20forecast%20for%20your%20location%20on%20the%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22http%3A%2F%2Fepa.gov%2Fsunsafety%2Fuv-index-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EEPA's%20website%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETo%20predict%20the%20intensity%20of%20UV%20radiation%2C%20the%20UV%20index%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.epa.gov%2Fsites%2Fproduction%2Ffiles%2Fdocuments%2Fuviguide.pdf%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Etakes%20into%20account%3C%2Fa%3E%3A%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3E%3Cstrong%3EThe%20time%20of%20day.%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20UV%20radiation%20is%20strongest%20between%2010%20am%20and%203%20pm%20when%20the%20sun%20is%20at%20its%20highest%20peak%20in%20the%20sky.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3E%3Cstrong%3EThe%20season.%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20UV%20radiation%20is%20highest%20in%20the%20spring%20and%20summer%20because%20this%20is%20when%20the%20northern%20hemisphere%20is%20tilted%20toward%20the%20sun.%20UV%20radiation%20declines%20in%20the%20fall%20and%20is%20lowest%20in%20the%20winter%20as%20the%20northern%20hemisphere%20tilts%20away%20from%20the%20sun.%C2%A0%C2%A0%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3E%3Cstrong%3ECloud%20cover.%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20Heavy%20clouds%20can%20block%20UV%20radiation%20and%20lower%20the%20UV%20index.%C2%A0%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3E%3Cstrong%3ELatitude%3C%2Fstrong%3E.%20Latitude%20measures%20how%20close%20you%20are%20to%20the%20equator.%20The%20closer%20to%20the%20equator%2C%20the%20more%20intense%20the%20UV%20radiation.%C2%A0%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3E%3Cstrong%3EAltitude%3C%2Fstrong%3E.%20The%20higher%20the%20elevation%2C%20the%20stronger%20the%20UV%20rays.%20In%20fact%2C%20UV%20increases%20about%202%25%20for%20every%201%2C000-foot%20elevation%20gain.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3E%3Cstrong%3EEnvironmental%20factors%3C%2Fstrong%3E.%20Trees%20or%20tall%20structures%20that%20block%20UV%20rays%20can%20lower%20UV%20radiation%20levels.%20On%20the%20other%20hand%2C%20reflective%20surfaces%2C%20like%20water%20and%20snow%20can%20intensify%20UV%20radiation.%C2%A0%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Caside%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EImportant%3A%20%3C%2Fstrong%3EUV%20rays%20can%20damage%20anyone%2C%20although%20the%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.epa.gov%2Fsites%2Fproduction%2Ffiles%2Fdocuments%2Fuviguide.pdf%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Erisks%20of%20sun%20exposure%20may%20differ%20by%20skin%20type%3C%2Fa%3E.%20For%20example%2C%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.cancer.org%2Fhealthy%2Fbe-safe-in-sun%2Fsun-damage.html%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Epeople%20with%20light%20skin%20are%20more%20likely%20to%20experience%20sunburns%20and%20skin%20cancer%3C%2Fa%3E%20than%20people%20with%20darker%20skin.%20People%20with%20lighter%20skin%20are%20therefore%20more%20susceptible%20to%20lower%20UV%20index%20scales.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Faside%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EUV%20Index%20of%200%20to%202%C2%A0%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EA%20UV%20index%20of%200%20to%202%20means%20you%20can%20expect%20a%20low%20level%20of%20UV%20radiation%20with%20minimal%20risk%20of%20getting%20sunburned%2C%20says%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.drjaliman.com%2Fabout%2Fdebra-jaliman-md%3Flayout%3Dedit%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EDebra%20Jaliman%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20MD%2C%20a%20dermatologist%20with%20her%20own%20private%20practice%20and%20an%20assistant%20professor%20of%20dermatology%20at%20the%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.mountsinai.org%2Fprofiles%2Fdebra-jaliman%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EIcahn%20School%20of%20Medicine%20at%20Mount%20Sinai%3C%2Fa%3E.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20the%20average%20person%20can%20lay%20in%20the%20sun%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.summithealthcare.com%2Fblog%2Fhow-much-sun-too-much-uv-index-explained%23%3A~%3Atext%3DA%2520UV%2520Index%2520of%25200%2Cprotected%2520from%2520prolonged%2520sun%2520exposure.%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Efor%20an%20hour%20without%20getting%20burnt%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20people%20with%20very%20fair%20skin%20should%20take%20precautions%20as%20they%20may%20burn%20within%2030%20minutes%2C%20says%20Jaliman.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Caside%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EQuick%20tip%3A%20%3C%2Fstrong%3EFor%20a%20UV%20index%20of%200%20to%202%2C%20the%20EPA%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.epa.gov%2Fsites%2Fproduction%2Ffiles%2Fdocuments%2Fuviguide.pdf%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Erecommends%3C%2Fa%3E%20wearing%20sunglasses%20and%20sunscreen%20with%20SPF%2030%20or%20more.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Faside%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EUV%20Index%20of%203%20to%205%C2%A0%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EThis%20is%20a%20moderate%20level%20of%20UV%20radiation%2C%20meaning%20there%20is%20a%20moderate%20risk%20of%20getting%20burnt%20if%20you%20are%20outside%20without%20sun%20protection.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20time%20it%20takes%20for%20your%20skin%20to%20burn%20at%20this%20level%20depends%20on%20your%20skin%20type%2C%20Jaliman%20says%2C%20but%20generally%20speaking%2C%20a%20UV%20index%20of%203%20to%205%20could%20result%20in%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fpdskin.com%2Fblogs%2Fuv-index-the-sun-safety-scale%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Esunburn%20in%20about%2030%20to%2045%20minutes%20on%20average%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETo%20protect%20your%20skin%2C%20the%20EPA%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.epa.gov%2Fsunsafety%2Fuv-index-scale-0%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Erecommends%3C%2Fa%3E%3A%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3ESeeking%20shade%20in%20the%20late%20morning%20through%20the%20mid-afternoon.%C2%A0%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EUsing%20sunscreen%20with%20at%20least%20SPF%2030%20on%20exposed%20skin.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EWearing%20a%20wide-brimmed%20hat%2C%20sunglasses%2C%20and%20protective%20clothing%20that%20helps%20block%20UV%20rays.%20This%20can%20include%20fabric%20with%20an%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.skincancer.org%2Fskin-cancer-prevention%2Fseal-of-recommendation%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eultraviolet%20protection%20factor%20(UPF)%20of%2030%20or%20more%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20which%20means%20it%20is%20tightly%20woven%20and%20helps%20block%20UV%20rays.%C2%A0%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EUV%20Index%20of%206%20to%207%C2%A0%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EThis%20is%20a%20high%20level%20of%20UV%20radiation%2C%20meaning%20the%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.azdhs.gov%2Fdocuments%2Fprevention%2Fnutrition-physical-activity%2Fempower%2Fresources-policies%2Fsunburn-card.pdf%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eaverage%20person%20is%20likely%20to%20burn%20in%20about%2015%20to%2025%20minutes%3C%2Fa%3E%20without%20sun%20protection.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAt%20this%20level%2C%20the%20EPA%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.epa.gov%2Fsites%2Fproduction%2Ffiles%2Fdocuments%2Fuviguide.pdf%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Erecommends%3C%2Fa%3E%3A%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3EApplying%20sunscreen%20with%20at%20least%20SPF%2030%20every%20two%20hours.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EWearing%20a%20wide-brimmed%20hat%2C%20sunglasses%2C%20and%20sun-protective%20clothing%2C%20like%20UPF%20fabric%20or%20long%20sleeves%20and%20pants.%C2%A0%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EAvoiding%20time%20in%20the%20sun%20during%20the%20hottest%20parts%20of%20the%20day%20%E2%80%94%20between%2010%20a.m%20and%203%20p.m.%20If%20you%20must%20be%20outside%20during%20this%20time%2C%20try%20to%20stay%20in%20the%20shade.%C2%A0%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EUV%20Index%20of%208%20to%2010%C2%A0%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EThis%20is%20a%20very%20high%20level%20of%20UV%20radiation%20with%20a%20high%20risk%20of%20getting%20sunburnt.%20On%20average%2C%20you%20can%20expect%20to%20burn%20in%20about%2010%20minutes%20or%20less%20at%20this%20level%20of%20UV%20radiation%2C%20Jaliman%20says.%20The%20EPA%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.epa.gov%2Fsites%2Fproduction%2Ffiles%2Fdocuments%2Fuviguide.pdf%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Erecommends%3C%2Fa%3E%20you%20take%20extra%20precautions%20if%20you%20are%20outside%2C%20including%20all%20the%20measures%20listed%20above.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BDo%20not%20go%20%5Boutside%5D%20without%20serious%20protection%2C%20or%20just%20do%20not%20go%20out%20at%20all%2C%26quot%3B%20Goldstein%20says.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EUV%20Index%20of%2011%2B%C2%A0%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EThis%20is%20an%20extreme%20level%20of%20UV%20radiation%20and%20sun%20exposure%20without%20protection%20at%20this%20level%20is%20dangerous.%20All%20precautions%20should%20be%20taken%2C%20including%20wearing%20sunscreen%2C%20sunglasses%2C%20a%20wide-brimmed%20hat%2C%20and%20protective%20clothing.%20At%20this%20level%2C%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.epa.gov%2Fsites%2Fproduction%2Ffiles%2Fdocuments%2Fuviguide.pdf%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eunprotected%20skin%20can%20burn%20in%20minutes%3C%2Fa%3E.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EOur%20top%20sunscreen%20picks%20to%20keep%20you%20protected%20at%20any%20UV%20index%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EIt's%20clear%20that%20no%20matter%20the%20UV%20index%2C%20your%20best%20bet%20is%20to%20use%20at%20least%20an%20SPF%2030%20when%20in%20sun%20exposure%20to%20stay%20optimally%20protected.%20We've%20tested%20the%20best%20sunscreens%20that%20offer%20lasting%2C%20comfortable%20coverage%20for%20any%20skin%20type.%20Whether%20you're%20looking%20for%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fguides%2Fbeauty%2Fbest-sunscreen-moisturizer%5C%22%3Ebest%20sunscreen%20moisturizer%3C%2Fa%3E%20specifically%20for%20the%20face%20or%20the%20best%20sunscreens%20for%20darker%20skin%20tones%2C%20our%20rigorous%20testing%20in%20sun%2C%20sweat%2C%20and%20water%20has%20put%20each%20of%20these%20at%20the%20top%20of%20our%20list.%20And%20don't%20forget%20about%20your%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fguides%2Fbeauty%2Fbest-lip-balm-spf%5C%22%3ESPF%20lip%20balms%3C%2Fa%3E%3B%20they're%20susceptible%20to%20burning%20as%20well.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EInsider's%20takeaway%C2%A0%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20UV%20index%20provides%20a%20measure%20of%20how%20strong%20UV%20rays%20are%20in%20a%20specific%20location.%20This%20information%20can%20help%20you%20plan%20when%20to%20spend%20time%20outside%20and%20what%20kind%20of%20sun%20protection%20to%20use.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EYour%20risk%20of%20burning%20increases%20the%20higher%20the%20UV%20index%20reads%2C%20Jaliman%20says%2C%20but%20regardless%20of%20what%20the%20index%20says%20you%20should%20always%20wear%20sun%20protection%20when%20spending%20time%20in%20the%20sun.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThis%20can%20include%20wearing%20sunscreen%20with%20at%20least%20SPF%2030%20or%20wearing%20protective%20clothing%2C%20like%20a%20hat%2C%20sunglasses%20or%20clothes%20with%20UPF%20fabric.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fguides%2Fbeauty%2Fuv-index-scale%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1720555942000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F668d928d3598be27b3453292%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fguides%2Fbeauty%2Fuv-index-scale%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20UV%20index%20scale%20rates%20how%20intense%20the%20sun's%20UV%20rays%20are%20on%20a%20particular%20day%2C%20which%20can%20help%20you%20decide%20what%20sun%20protection%20measures%20to%20take.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22insider%40insider.com%20(Erin%20Heger%2CJason%20R.%20McKnight)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A15%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fguides%2Fbeauty%2Fuv-index-scale%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A